The paper deals with the distributed selection problem, which is a problem in distributed computing. Therefore, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves sorting networks and comparisons, which are topics in algorithms and data structures, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of messages and communication networks, which falls under cs.Distributed (Distributed Computing). The paper involves the simulation of a sorting network, which is a topic in algorithms, making cs.AL (Computational Complexity) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the lower bound of basic data aggregation problems, which involves information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible sub-category as well.
